query:
SELECT min(i_item_sk) ,
       min(w_warehouse_name) ,
       min(d1.d_week_seq) ,
       min(cs_item_sk) ,
       min(cs_order_number) ,
       min(inv_item_sk)
FROM catalog_sales
JOIN inventory ON (cs_item_sk = inv_item_sk)
JOIN warehouse ON (w_warehouse_sk=inv_warehouse_sk)
JOIN item ON (i_item_sk = cs_item_sk)
JOIN customer_demographics ON (cs_bill_cdemo_sk = cd_demo_sk)
JOIN household_demographics ON (cs_bill_hdemo_sk = hd_demo_sk)
JOIN date_dim d1 ON (cs_sold_date_sk = d1.d_date_sk)
JOIN date_dim d2 ON (inv_date_sk = d2.d_date_sk)
JOIN date_dim d3 ON (cs_ship_date_sk = d3.d_date_sk)
LEFT OUTER JOIN promotion ON (cs_promo_sk=p_promo_sk)
LEFT OUTER JOIN catalog_returns ON (cr_item_sk = cs_item_sk
                                    AND cr_order_number = cs_order_number)
WHERE d1.d_week_seq = d2.d_week_seq
  AND inv_quantity_on_hand < cs_quantity
  AND d3.d_date > d1.d_date + interval '3 day'
  AND hd_buy_potential = 'Unknown'
  AND d1.d_year = 2001
  AND cd_marital_status = 'U'
  AND cd_dep_count BETWEEN 5 AND 6
  AND i_category IN ('Home                                              ', 'Home                                              ', 'Shoes')
  AND cs_wholesale_cost BETWEEN 32 AND 89  ;
plan_content: /*+  SeqScan(catalog_sales) SeqScan(household_demographics) SeqScan(item) SeqScan(d1) IndexScan(customer_demographics customer_demographics_pkey) SeqScan(d2) SeqScan(warehouse) IndexScan(inventory inventory_pkey) IndexScan(d3 date_dim_pkey) HashJoin(catalog_sales household_demographics) HashJoin(catalog_sales household_demographics item) HashJoin(catalog_sales household_demographics item d1) NestLoop(catalog_sales household_demographics item d1 customer_demographics) HashJoin(catalog_sales household_demographics item d1 customer_demographics d2) NestLoop(warehouse inventory) NestLoop(catalog_sales household_demographics item d1 customer_demographics d2 warehouse inventory) NestLoop(catalog_sales household_demographics item d1 customer_demographics d2 warehouse inventory d3) Leading((((((((catalog_sales household_demographics) item) d1) customer_demographics) d2) (warehouse inventory)) d3)) */

       min(w_warehouse_name) ,
       min(d1.d_week_seq) ,
       min(cs_item_sk) ,
       min(cs_order_number) ,
       min(inv_item_sk)
FROM catalog_sales
JOIN inventory ON (cs_item_sk = inv_item_sk)
JOIN warehouse ON (w_warehouse_sk=inv_warehouse_sk)
JOIN item ON (i_item_sk = cs_item_sk)
JOIN customer_demographics ON (cs_bill_cdemo_sk = cd_demo_sk)
JOIN household_demographics ON (cs_bill_hdemo_sk = hd_demo_sk)
JOIN date_dim d1 ON (cs_sold_date_sk = d1.d_date_sk)
JOIN date_dim d2 ON (inv_date_sk = d2.d_date_sk)
JOIN date_dim d3 ON (cs_ship_date_sk = d3.d_date_sk)
LEFT OUTER JOIN promotion ON (cs_promo_sk=p_promo_sk)
LEFT OUTER JOIN catalog_returns ON (cr_item_sk = cs_item_sk
                                    AND cr_order_number = cs_order_number)
WHERE d1.d_week_seq = d2.d_week_seq
  AND inv_quantity_on_hand < cs_quantity
  AND d3.d_date > d1.d_date + interval '3 day'
  AND hd_buy_potential = 'Unknown'
  AND d1.d_year = 2001
  AND cd_marital_status = 'M'
  AND cd_dep_count BETWEEN 1 AND 1
  AND i_category IN ('Children                                          ', 'Electronics                                       ', 'Home')
  AND cs_wholesale_cost BETWEEN 27 AND 94  ;
plan_content: /*+  SeqScan(catalog_sales) SeqScan(household_demographics) SeqScan(item) SeqScan(d1) IndexScan(customer_demographics customer_demographics_pkey) SeqScan(d2) SeqScan(warehouse) IndexScan(inventory inventory_pkey) IndexScan(d3 date_dim_pkey) HashJoin(catalog_sales household_demographics) HashJoin(catalog_sales household_demographics item) HashJoin(catalog_sales household_demographics item d1) NestLoop(catalog_sales household_demographics item d1 customer_demographics) HashJoin(catalog_sales household_demographics item d1 customer_demographics d2) NestLoop(warehouse inventory) NestLoop(catalog_sales household_demographics item d1 customer_demographics d2 warehouse inventory) NestLoop(catalog_sales household_demographics item d1 customer_demographics d2 warehouse inventory d3) Leading((((((((catalog_sales household_demographics) item) d1) customer_demographics) d2) (warehouse inventory)) d3)) */
